programme.title: Wildest Africa: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile

programme.sub-title: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Nile: An African Odyssey
programme.desc: The Nile is the longest river in the world. Ancient Egypt, one of the history's most powerful civilizations, depended hugely upon it. Each year, it flooded, replenishing the fields with fertile silt. This automatic irrigation fueled Egypt's economy.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Cape Coast: Where Worlds Colide

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Japan: Islands of Extremes
programme.desc: Japan's 7,000 islands stretch for over 2,400 km, and cover an incredible range of climates. Winter in the central and northern islands can be savage, but summer in the sweltering southern islands couldn't be more different.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Okavango: Water in the Desert

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Vancouver Island: Rivers of Life
programme.desc: Vancouver island is the largest island off the west coast of North America. Glaciers fuel the flow of some of Canada's tallest waterfalls, and an endless network of rivers and creeks provides the ideal habitat for the pacific salmon.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise

programme.sub-title: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Sri Lanka: Monsoon Island

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Falkland Islands: Penguin Paradise

programme.title: World's Greatest: Drives
programme.desc: A journey by road expands our horizons, allowing us to explore the depth and breadth of whole countries and continents, stopping whenever and wherever we chose.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanoes
programme.desc: There are few sights on earth as compelling as a volcanic eruption. Volcanoes have the potential to cause death and widespread destruction in a heartbeat, but they also give rise to new life and ecosystems.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mega Cities
programme.desc: Mega Cities provide a bustling home to populations of over 10 million. Travel from the high-density living of Shanghai and Bangkok to the sprawling cities of Delhi and Mexico City, each the backdrop for dynamic cultures.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Lost Cities
programme.desc: Once powerful and populous centers of influence, these lost cities are providing clues to how our ancestors existed in the world and remind us that ancient civilizations were not so far removed from our own.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mountains
programme.desc: The earth’s fragile crust has folded and faulted, and nowhere are these natural forces more evident than in the world’s great mountains. Explore the highest peaks of the world’s terrain - the rugged realm between heaven and earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Global Cities
programme.desc: Travel to the centers of wealth, power, industry, and innovation. From London to Tokyo, Hong Kong to New York, these are the cities that never sleep. The influence held in these economic hubs unites the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Capital Cities
programme.desc: With visionaries, politicians, and activists, these metropolises are defined as the official seats of government. Dublin, Washington, and Taipei share broad avenues, museums, and monuments, but are as varied as the countries they represent.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Wetland Animals
programme.desc: Wetland Animals dives into the swamps, rivers, and flood plains of the Everglades, Botswana’s Okavango Delta, Kakadu National Park in Australia, and the Amazon to see deadly crocodiles, piranhas, hippopotamus, flamingo, manatee, and platypus.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Nations
programme.desc: Though many are small in stature, they have punched well above their weight on the global stage. Some are rooted in ancient history, while others are only just beginning to realize their full potential.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mega Cities
programme.desc: Mega Cities provide a bustling home to populations of over 10 million. Travel from the high-density living of Shanghai and Bangkok to the sprawling cities of Delhi and Mexico City, each the backdrop for dynamic cultures.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coral Islands
programme.desc: The reef systems that gave rise to coral islands support the vast majority of marine species on our planet, but they are under threat. Explore the delicate balance between exploiting and preserving these extraordinary natural wonders.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Lost Cities
programme.desc: Once powerful and populous centers of influence, these lost cities are providing clues to how our ancestors existed in the world and remind us that ancient civilizations were not so far removed from our own.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: NEW: Great Tank Battles of World War II
programme.desc: This first part of the series introduces the first tanks being deployed on the battlefields in northern France during WWI and describes the devastating effect these steel monsters had on an infantry confronted with them for the very first time.

programme.title: Gestapo: Hitler's Secret Police
programme.desc: Hermann Goering’s Secret State Police were tasked to arrest and torture confessions and information from supposed enemies of the Reich.

programme.title: Embedded 45' - Shooting War in Germany: Embedded 45 - Shooting War in Germany 2
programme.desc: This second episode covers the last week of March to late April. The cameramen covered many stories of victory and defeat, death and liberation. Faces of despair and joy, scenes of war and peace.

programme.title: Embedded 45' - Shooting War in Germany: Embedded 45 - Shooting War in Germany 1
programme.desc: This first episode covers the last week of February to late March. When American troops started their final invasion of Nazi Germany in February 1945, U.S. Army cameramen were at their side.

programme.title: Destroy Paris: Hitler's Secret Plan
programme.desc: By 1944, as the Reich was crumbling, Hitler gave detailed orders for the destruction of Paris. He wanted the monuments and all the bridges mined and the city reduced to a 'pile of rubble'.

programme.title: Battle of Britain: The Race For Radar
programme.desc: On the brink of war the Germans mount a daring Zeppelin spy mission. Had the Luftwaffe spies discovered Britain’s greatest secret?'

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: U-Boat War
programme.desc: U-boats posed the deadliest threat to Allied convoys traveling the Atlantic.

programme.title: War Story: Where Hell is: The Leopold and the Scheldt
programme.desc: The Allies liberated Antwerp, the world’s largest deep-water port, on 4 September 1944, but it could only be accessed via the Scheldt Estuary, the perfect place for the Germans to make a stand.
programme.sub-title: Where Hell is: The Leopold and the Scheldt

programme.title: War Story: Falaise, the corridor of death
programme.desc: The Canadian army played the pivotal role in closing the Falaise Gap and ensuring Allied victory in the Normandy Campaign in August 1944.

programme.title: War Story: D-Day plus 1
programme.desc: The Canadian stand against the 12th SS Panzer Division Hitlerjugend immediately after D-Day allowed the Allies to switch to the offensive and truly begin the liberation of Europe.

programme.title: War Story: Surviving Dieppe
programme.desc: The Dieppe assault of 19 August 1942 is the worst day in Canadian military history: in just 8 hours, 907 Canadians were killed. For 2,000 of their comrades, nearly three years of incarceration in German prison camps followed.

programme.title: War Story: Whistle for a Tiffy
programme.desc: From D-Day, Tactical Air Force fighter-bombers played a pivotal role in Allied battlefield success; Canadian soldiers knew they could always “whistle for a Tiffy”.

programme.title: War Story: Behind Enemy Lines
programme.desc: Royal Canadian Air Force bombing operations play a crucial role in disrupting German infrastructure ahead of the Normandy invasion of June 1944. In the process, dozens of Canadian airmen are forced to bail out over occupied Belgium and France.

programme.title: War Story: Not One Step Back: The Battle of Stalingrad
programme.desc: In the summer of 1942, the Germans advance to seize the rich oilfields of the Caucasus. In their path, the city of Stalingrad, its Soviet defenders personally ordered by Stalin to “take not one step back".
programme.sub-title: Not One Step Back: The Battle of Stalingrad

programme.title: War Story: Buchenwald Airmen
programme.desc: For two months in 1944, 168 Allied airmen were shot down over occupied France, betrayed to the Gestapo by the same collaborator, transported to the Nazi concentration and slave labour camp Buchenwald.

programme.title: War Story: The Last Ship: The Sinking of the Esquimalt
programme.desc: On 16 April 1945, a mere three weeks before German surrender, the submarine fired a single torpedo that sank the last Canadian naval vessel lost to enemy action.
programme.sub-title: The Last Ship: The Sinking of the Esquimalt

programme.title: War Story: Prisoners of the Sun
programme.desc: On 16 November 1941, two Canadian battalions arrived in the British colony of Hong Kong. Their aim: Bolster the Empire’s defenses in the event of aggression by the restless forces of Japan, stationed only kilometres away in occupied China.

programme.title: War Story: Vengeance
programme.desc: In 1941, nearly 30,000 Jews escaped the ghettos and work camps and they joined the growing underground resistance army, actively fighting the Nazis.

programme.title: War Story: Across the Rhine: Paras in Germany
programme.desc: In mid-September 1944, the remnants of the battered 1st Canadian Parachute Battalion participated in the largest parachute drop in history, fought a successful battle.
programme.sub-title: Across the Rhine: Paras in Germany

programme.title: War Story: Out of the Clouds: Paras in Normandy
programme.desc: In Normandy, the 1st Canadian Parachute Battalion proved itself to be in the vanguard of the best-trained and toughest units in the Allied forces.
programme.sub-title: Out of the Clouds: Paras in Normandy

programme.title: War Story: The Road to Rome
programme.desc: The Road to Rome examines the incredible experiences of Canadian veterans, the victories and horrors of armoured combat, and the pivotal value, far too often neglected, of the overall Italian Campaign.

programme.title: War Story: Ortona: The War Inside
programme.desc: The War Inside is a personal retelling of one of the fiercest battles of the Italian Campaign from the searing points of view of Canadian infantrymen, a tanker, a stretcher bearer, and a German paratrooper.

programme.title: War Story: Sicily: The First Campaign
programme.desc: The Sicily Campaign began with the largest seaborne invasion in history on 9-10 July 1943. The Allied forces of Britain, Canada, and the United States sought to knock Italy out of the war and attack Germany from the south.

programme.title: War Story: Bomb Girls Remember
programme.desc: During the Second World War, 250,000 Canadian women helped to build the arsenal of democracy. These young women met the challenges of factory work and helped to win the Second World War, and by doing so, paved the way for future generations.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Getting Home
programme.desc: In this film, Bomber Command personnel and a Luftwaffe pilot take the viewer through the frightening reality of fighting in the skies as they try to get a damaged bomber home.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Hitting Back
programme.desc: After surviving the German bombing campaign of British cities, RAF Bomber Command struck back against Germany. The devastating consequences of raids, for both for the young men in the skies and the people on the ground, are portrayed in this film.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Japan continues its suicidal resistance, and invading it looks costly. After 2 atomic bombs, the Emperor intervenes and stops the War. Stalin grabs territory in East Asia. The War is over, and the Atomic Era and the Cold War start.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: In 1945, Germany is crumbly on both fronts. The Western Allies cross the Rhine and take most of Germany, while the Red Army quickly advances into Berlin. After Hitler's suicide, Germany surrenders and is divided among the allied powers.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Lost Continent (Atlantis)
programme.desc: As the Nazis rose to power, Himmler and the SS were convinced Atlantis could be found, and instigated a series of archeological expeditions seeking uncover and exploit its secrets.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Walking with Witches
programme.desc: Convinced the medieval witch trials were a Judeo-Christian attempt to exterminate the Aryans, Himmler established a special team led by Reinhard Heydrich to build a database of medieval German witchcraft practices.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Quest for the Holy Grail
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.
programme.sub-title: The Quest for the Holy Grail

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Into the Mountains (Tibet)
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Cro Magnon
programme.desc: The debate about humanity's true origins becomes a nefarious fixation as SS leader Heinrich Himmler turns his attention to proving the Paleolithic past of Germany's Aryan race.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Runes
programme.desc: Runes are the letters of an ancient Germanic writing system that harkens back to a mythological age filled with heroes, magic, and mystery.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: X-Rated
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler had a depraved sex life that he tried to keep hidden from the German public. He was said to be a chronic masturbator, a voyeur and that he engaged in sado-masochistic sex with women.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Body Image
programme.desc: Hitler wanted the world to believe he possessed super-human qualities but in private he was a wreck. This episode reveals the archives that confirm Hitler’s genital deformity, the alarming truth about his heavy drug addiction and the Parkinson’s.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Family Matters
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler's father was a violent, abusive man. His mother doted on her young son. This episode delves deep into the psychology of Hitler as the narcissistic child who grew into a malignant psychopath full of rage and deep hatred.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Suicidal Maidens
programme.desc: Using extensive archival research, this program explores the squalid secrets he lied and killed to protect

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Adolf Hitler
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler: The film explores the roots of Adolf Hitler and traces the story of his life from the town of his birth to his final days.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.
programme.desc: From the Protection Squadron to the SS State: Trace the rise to power of the SS as we examine several perpetrators. Who was recruited? And why was the SS attractive to men?
programme.sub-title: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Heinrich Himmler
programme.desc: Heinrich Himmler: An agriculturalist by trade, he went on to lead the SS and tried to escape responsibility at the end of the war. Who was Heinrich Himmler?

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich
programme.desc: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich: More than any other Nazi leader, Heydrich was an orchestrator of mass murder, and was terrifyingly clinical in approach.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Waffen-SS
programme.desc: The Waffen-SS: Masqueraded as military excellence, the reality was very different. Recruits were poorly trained and remorse was nonexistent, as SS troops killed mercilessly.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The SS Death Head's Unit
programme.desc: The SS Death Head's Unit: Tasked with guarding concentration camps, this unit's actions knew no bounds, and, despite their heinous acts, still attended social gatherings.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945
programme.desc: Unrepentant: The SS and Its Myth After 1945: Drawing a line to the present, the atrocities of the SS are beyond all doubt, yet, there is a cult surrounding 'old comrades' today.
programme.sub-title: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922
programme.desc: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922: In the wake of the First World War, Adolf Hitler identifies Benito Mussolini as his model and has one ultimate goal: to gain power in Germany.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928
programme.desc: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928: Hitler appears to be eliminated after his failed putsch in 1923. Discover how the Nazi movement used democracy's tolerance in Germany to come back.

programme.desc: Laramy shows us how hunting was done in the mid-1800s by the Mountain Men, where unusual skills and stalking techniques were needed to survive throughout the winter. Harsh Winters were known as "White Death" to the Mountain Men.
programme.sub-title: The Hunt of a Mountain Man

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: In this third season, a group of men and a group of women are abandoned on the opposite side of the same island. Neither knows the other is there. Will these two small groups survive - and what will happen when they meet?

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: The women catch sight of a man in the distance, and when they go to investigate the two groups finally meet. But as a vicious tropical storm rolls in, the thunder and lightning have a devastating effect on amputee and war veteran Hannah.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: Marooned for ten days, the islanders now face starvation. They battle dangerous ocean currents to set fishing nets. Rob develops a tooth abscess, and endures primitive surgery on the beach. And flickers of romance begin.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: Tempers reach fever pitch when Tilly turns on Erika. Dan leads an expedition for food around the rocky coastline. With the tide coming in he must make a difficult decision: do they turn back or risk their lives crossing one last perilous set of rocks?

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: After Patrick's fall, the rest of the group face a terrifying ordeal trying to escape the oncoming sea. Back in camp, the men have been dominating hunting so far - but Tilly decides to venture into the jungle in search of prey.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: The Islanders are barely managing to survive and some of the men’s bodies are starting to fail them. The women continue to look for food and Simon leads a hunt into the jungle for the most dangerous predator on the island: the caiman crocodile.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: In this special episode of The Island with Bear Grylls, Bear takes an in-depth look at how the castaways survived.

programme.title: Survivorman
programme.desc: Les travels to India to survive with no food, no water, no shelter and no camera crew. Leopards, snakes, territorial honey bees and the infamous Royal Bengal tiger all pose threats to Les's survival.

programme.title: Survivorman
programme.desc: From over 200 applicants, Joe McConnell was selected to join Les on what proves to be a very difficult survival expedition.

programme.title: Survivorman
programme.desc: Les Stroud has survived in the most challenging environments on the planet, but few compare to the isolation and disorientation he experiences surviving in Romania's Transylvanian Alps.

programme.title: Survivorman
programme.desc: Les simulates being medically stranded and lost in the Transylvanian Alps to test the skills of Romania's top Search and Rescue Team. He feels totally trapped by a simulated splintered leg.

programme.title: Survivorman
programme.desc: Forced to land his ultralight aircraft due to miscalculation in fuel, Survivorman is once again out to endure the elements for seven days in this spectacular locale… the Australia Outback.

programme.title: Survivorman
programme.desc: Survivorman has always been to teach the right way, the safe way, to instruct outdoor enthusiasts on when not take chances and not go over the top, to avoid landing oneself in peril.

programme.title: Survivorman
programme.desc: Les strands himself on purpose, accompanied by his long-time survival buddy Bob Wilson, on a deserted island in the Kingdom of Tonga.

programme.title: Modern Marvels

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Alexander Graham Bell races Elisha Gray to patent the telephone.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: A countdown of the top gizmos and gadgets featured on "Modern Marvels," from golden oldies to newfangled thingamabobs, including an electronic doodad that was once considered a threat to national security.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Mankind makes use of lead, a versatile but toxic metal, for 6,000 years; mining; car battery factory; specialists remove harmful lead objects from homes and businesses; lead makes crystal sparkle.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Stories of those who believed in dreams and defied the commonplace with their extraordinary creations; covering some of the world's architectural and engineering structures, scientific inventions, and social wonders.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Sun-screens; surfboards; the boardwalk; coolers; hibachis; dune buggies; wave runners.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: The most dangerous snakes, sports, weather events; America's most dangerous volcano; tornado hazards; base jumping.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: PONG; microprocessors; Texas Instruments; Mr. Coffee; the microwave oven; Polaroid.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: New and exciting gadgets of the 1980s.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Visionaries enlarge, reinforce and motorize balloons and blimps, giving birth to the airship; 161 rigid airships are built before spectacular crashes, including the Hindenburg disaster, put an end to the era.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: The Alaska pipeline carries crude oil 800 miles across the state.

programme.title: Modern Marvels

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Congressional mandate creates the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers to respond to the nation's engineering needs.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: An underground subway system transforms the bustling metropolis of Athens, Greece, alleviating chronic traffic problems, meeting the needs of the 2004 Olympics and uncovering thousands of invaluable artifacts.

programme.title: Modern Marvels

programme.desc: The Wilson Sporting Goods football factory; Rawlings' Costa Rica baseball factory; the National Soccer Hall of Fame; the National Baseball Hall of Fame.

programme.title: Modern Marvels
programme.desc: Bathroom technology; Kohler makes a digitally controlled shower complete with steam, music and LED chromatherapy; manufacturing sinks; "uncloggable" toilet; the engineering behind low-flow showers and toilets.

programme.title: Listening For Something Adrienne Rich And Dionne Brand In Conversation
programme.desc: The nation, the country, where do we belong in it? In this film through conversation and poetry two poets meet for the telling and the listening. Topics include political issues, feminism, racism and lesbianism, among others.

programme.title: Danish Poet, The
programme.desc: Can we trace the chain of events that leads to our own birth? Is our existence just coincidence? The Danish Poet considers these questions as we follow a poet whose creative well has run dry, on a holiday to Norway to meet a famous writer.

programme.title: Rusting World
programme.desc: The scene is a desolate landscape that reveals no signs of life. Out of the stillness emerge two opposing factions, both wanting possession of a shiny object. This allegorical film suggests a decaying world created by greed

programme.title: Illuminated Lives A Brief History Of Womens Work In The Middle Ages
programme.desc: The popular image of the Middle Ages comes from fairy tales and romances. This animated short challenges some enduring myths about medieval women and shows what their lives were really like.

programme.title: The Stratford Adventure
programme.desc: How a small Canadian city, bearing the name of Stratford and by a river Avon, realized the vision of one of its sons: the creation of a theatre for the staging of the finest Shakespearean drama.

programme.title: Julie Obrien
programme.desc: This film is loosely structured around Julie O'Brien, eleven’s school assignment to write an essay about the old times in Newfoundland, how they have changed, how they are still remembered.

programme.title: A Mother And Daughter On Abortion
programme.desc: The document of an intimate conversation between a mother and her adult daughter. They speak candidly about their personal experiences in trying to obtain an abortion, and how, in different decade, each got caught up in the system and its rules.

programme.title: The Railrodder
programme.desc: A screen short starring Buster Keaton, this is one of the last films of the comedian's long career. As "the railrodder" he crosses Canada from east to west on a railway track speeder. As might be expected, the film is full of sight gags.

programme.title: Universe
programme.desc: This cinematic masterpiece inspired Stanley Kubrick's "2001: A Space Odyssey." Realistic animation explores distant galaxies beyond the reach of telescopes, immersing viewers in awe-inspiring cosmic vistas.

programme.title: Churchills Island
programme.desc: A classic presentation of the strategy of the Battle of Britain, the film shows, with penetrating clarity, the relationship of the various forces that went to make up the island's defenses. The first NFB film to win an Oscar.

programme.title: What Walaa Wants
programme.desc: Raised in a West Bank refugee camp while her mother was in prison, Walaa is determined to become a policewoman in the Palestinian Security Forces—not easy for a girl who breaks all the rules.

programme.title: Special Delivery
programme.desc: The first big mistake Ralph makes is not clearing the snow from the front walk, and his life goes downhill from that point on. By the end of the story, the mailman has fatally slipped on his job, and Alice, his wife, doesn't live there anymore.

programme.title: Goddess Remembered
programme.desc: This poetic documentary is a salute to 35 000 years of "pre-history," to the values of ancestors only recently remembered, and to the goddess-worshipping religions of the ancient past.

programme.title: Hands Of History
programme.desc: In this acclaimed 1994 documentary, Loretta Todd, a leading figure in Indigenous cinema in Canada, profiles four contemporary female artists.The film is a moving testimony to the vital role Indigenous women play in nurturing Indigenous cultures.

programme.title: Sea Dream
programme.desc: Children, like adults, have days that go wrong. This film shows how one little girl overcomes the day's frustrations by diving into an underwater fantasy where she spends time with her friend, the lady octopus.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Women At Work
programme.desc: This is an abridged version of a film made in 1958. The greater part of the film accepts as normal the waste of women's talents in repetitive or service jobs, while elevating this work to the status of a career.

programme.title: Neighbours Voisins
programme.desc: Two neighbours live side by side in harmony until a flower grows on the dividing line between their properties. Who does it belong to? The argument that follows ends up with both neighbours in their graves. The most famous of Norman McLaren’s films.

programme.title: Nobody Waved Good-Bye
programme.desc: A story of teenage conflict--the predicament of a youth who rebels against his parents' middle-class goals and conventions but finds the world, away from home and high school, a cold place to go it alone.

programme.title: King Of The Hill
programme.desc: Spring 1972. The Chicago Cubs are poised to win the National League's Pennant race, lead by their star pitcher, a Black Canadian named Ferguson Jenkins, who was inducted into the Baseball Hall of Fame in 1991. This is his story.

programme.title: Sun Wind And Wood
programme.desc: People combat high energy costs with inventive solar, wind, and wood solutions. This film showcases experiments like the Ark, a bio-shelter sustaining a family with housing, heat, food, and electricity using natural systems.

programme.title: Mother Earth/La Terre Notre Mere
programme.desc: Mother Earth is a short, evocative, poetic film that celebrates life on our planet. This documentary film looks at the reality of human beings; the earth is our home and we are profoundly connected to all other beings.

programme.title: Tu As Crie Let Me Go
programme.desc: In "Tu as crié LET ME GO," Anne Claire Poirier explores her daughter's tragic descent into drugs and prostitution, seeking understanding of the societal pressures influencing young people's risky behaviors in Montreal's streets.

programme.title: Benoit
programme.desc: Benoît is an astonishingly accomplished eleven-year-old Québécois from Joliette. He pursues such diverse activities as weight lifting and playing the violin.

programme.title: Physics Of Sorrow, The
programme.desc: The Physics of Sorrow tracks an unknown man’s life as he sifts through memories of his youth in Bulgaria through to his increasingly rootless and melancholic adulthood in Canada.

programme.title: Beyond Paper
programme.desc: In the era of the digital revolution, the transmission of knowledge is going through a profound upheaval as humanity’s archives migrate from paper to the cloud. How can we grasp the impact of the ongoing abandonment of books on thought and learning?

programme.title: Christmas in Boston
programme.desc: Gina und Seth sind seit ihrer Kindheit Brieffreunde, haben sich aber noch nie getroffen. Als sie sich endlich dazu entschließen, sich zu treffen, braucht es allerdings ein wenig Weihnachtszauber, um ihre Liebe füreinander aufzudecken.

programme.title: Broadcasting Christmas
programme.desc: Als ihr Sendeparyner beschliebt, Amerikas beliebteste Morgensendung zu verlassen, kundigt Veronika Daniels an, dass sie ihren neuen Co-Moderator aus einer Handvoll Kandidten auswahlen wird, zu denen auch Charlie Fisher.

programme.title: Christmas Encore
programme.desc: Charlotte Lacy ist eine verzweifelte Schauspielerin, die die Hauptrolle in einer Produktion von "A Christmas Carol" ergattert. Sie und der Regisseur haben jedoch viele unterschiedliche kreative Vorstellungen.

programme.title: Eine Hochzeit an Weihnachten
programme.desc: Haley Foster entkam ihrer Kleinstadt-Kindheit in Pineridge und baute sich ein Großstadtleben in Los Angeles als Top-Hochzeitsplanerin in einer elitären und mächtigen Firma auf, die von Frau Reynolds geleitet wird.

programme.title: Weihnachten in Alaska
programme.desc: Als die Geschäftsfrau Jennifer erfährt, dass ihre Eltern in den Ferien ohne sie unterwegs sein werden, beschließt sie, ihr geschäftiges Stadtleben in San Francisco zu verlassen, um das Gasthaus ihrer Großmutter zu besuchen.

programme.title: Der Weihnachts-Song
programme.desc: Budgetkürzungen zwingen zwei New Yorker Hochschulen zu fusionieren. Ein Musiklehrer und eine Lehrerin konkurrieren im größten Weihnachts-Song Wettbewerb des Landes um die Arbeitsstelle des...

programme.title: Christmas Land
programme.desc: Christmas Land hat seit dem tragischen Tod von Glinda schon bessere Tage gesehen, und Jules muss viele komplizierte Entscheidungen treffen.

programme.title: Die Weihnachtstruppe
programme.desc: Die arbeitslose Kunstlehrerin Allie möchte Witwer Gordon und seine Töchter wieder für Weihnachten begeistern.

programme.title: Der magische Weihnachtsschmuck
programme.desc: Seit sie an Weihnachten sitzen gelassen wurde, hat Marie (Jessica Lowndes) mit dem Fest der Liebe abgeschlossen. Daran kann auch der Festtagsschmuck nichts ändern, den ihre Mutter ihr täglich zukommen lässt.

programme.title: Ein perfektes Weihnachten
programme.desc: Holly Maddux fehlt zu ihrem Glück nur noch der perfekte Mann. Nach einem Sturz vor dem Geschäft schwebt Holly im siebten Himmel, denn ihr Traummann steht plötzlich vor ihr...

programme.title: Weihnachten in den Highlands
programme.desc: Dieses Weihnachten wird Blair Henderson, eine Parfümexpertin aus New York, von ihrer Chefin ins ferne Schottland geschickt, um einen seltenen Duft zu finden.

programme.title: Mein Weihnachtstraum
programme.desc: Um sich vor der gefürchteten Besitzerin eines Kaufhauses in Paris zu beweisen, bittet Managerin Christina den kürzlich gefeuerten Kurt um Hilfe in der Weihnachtszeit. Als die beiden sich näher kommen, muss Christina eine schwere Wahl treffen...

programme.title: Ein Pferd für Lizzy – Mein Freund fürs Leben
programme.desc: Die rebellische Teenagerin Lizzy wird von ihren Eltern an Weihnachten widerwillig auf die Pferderanch ihrer Großmutter geschickt. Die Großmutter weiß, dass Lizzy ein großartiges Mädchen ist und vertraut ihr die Pflege eines Pferdes namens Hope...

programme.title: Alle hassen Chris: Chris hasst Weihnachten
programme.desc: Weihnachten steht kurz bevor, doch so richtig freuen kann sich die Familie nicht, denn so wie es aussieht werden Weihnachtsgeschenke in diesem Jahr finanziell nicht drin sein...

programme.title: Weihnachten mit Hindernissen
programme.desc: Vicky und Jason haben sich schon längst getrennt. Aber ihre beiden Kinder bringen sie dazu, die Weihnachtsferien gemeinsam zu verbringen. Als dann auch noch Vickys Boss und Jasons Assistentin auftauchen, wird es immer turbulenter...

programme.title: Auf der Suche nach dem Weihnachtsmann
programme.desc: Wer glaubt denn heute noch an den Weihnachtsmann? Der 11-jährige Danny tut das. Mithilfe kleiner technischer Spielereien möchte er Santas Existenz wissenschaftlich beweisen. Zusammen mit seinen Freunden macht sich Danny auf in ein spannendes...

programme.title: Die Nanny
programme.desc: Fran hofft auf ein Wunder, als Maxwell, Grace und C.C. nach einem Autounfall vermisst werden.

programme.title: Mein Weihnachtstraum
programme.desc: Um sich vor der gefürchteten Besitzerin eines Kaufhauses in Paris zu beweisen, bittet Managerin Christina den kürzlich gefeuerten Kurt um Hilfe in der Weihnachtszeit. Als die beiden sich näher kommen, muss Christina eine schwere Wahl treffen...

programme.title: Melrose Place: Weihnachtsgefühle
programme.desc: Alison muss sich von ihrer Operation erholen. Billy kümmert sich um sie, allerdings etwas überfürsorglich. Jake versucht derweil, Jo näher zu kommen, doch sie braucht noch Zeit, um nachzudenken.

programme.title: Alone for Christmas
programme.desc: Wenn eine Familie an Heiligabend das Haus von Oma besucht, lässt sie ihren Hund allein zu Hause. Und wenn Einbrecher versuchen, die Geschenke unter dem Baum hervorzuholen, um sie zu stoppen.

programme.title: Ein perfektes Weihnachten

programme.title: Auf der Suche nach dem Weihnachtsmann

programme.title: Sobrevivendo Às Festas com Parentes
programme.desc: As irmãs Miranda e Lyla se reúnem para o Natal com suas famílias. Ao longo de três dias, alegria e caos causam estragos nos planos de férias das famílias e as antigas rivalidades entre irmãos surgem para sabotar a esperança diversão de fim de ano.

programme.title: Um Natal Encantado
programme.desc: Hugo, de doze anos, ainda acredita em elfos, mas é provocado por seus colegas, então decide se forçar a crescer. Mas quando sua família sai de férias de Natal, ele descobre que elfos moram no hotel.

programme.title: O Desejo de Charlie
programme.desc: Um veterano militar volta para casa depois de um afastamento por estresse pós-traumático. Com seu novo cachorro, ele descobre em pleno Natal um novo propósito em sua vida - auxiliar ex-militares que precisam de ajuda.

programme.title: Tempo de Natal
programme.desc: Dois irmãos distantes tentam se reconectar no Natal, mas há algo que um deles não consegue superar: o outro pensa que é um viajante do tempo.

programme.title: Véspera de Natal
programme.desc: É véspera de Natal e um apagão vai obrigar alguns nova-iorquinos ocupados a ficarem presos dentro de elevadores enquanto esperam por ajuda. Essa longa noite juntos irá mudar suas vidas para sempre.

programme.title: O Projeto de Natal
programme.desc: Quatro irmãos unem forças para se vingar dos Hagbarts, os valentões mais malvados de sua escola.

programme.title: Dançando No Natal
programme.desc: Olívia, professora de ballet, escolhe a talentosa Lily como protagonista do espetáculo de Natal "O Quebra-Nozes" e acaba se apaixonando pelo pai dela, Michael, um bombeiro atraente. Com a ajuda dele, Olívia tentará salvar seu estúdio de dança.

programme.title: Bailey, Um Herói do Natal
programme.desc: É "época de Natal" e Bailey, preocupado em não receber presentes por ter sido um cachorro mau, descobre sobre um misterioso índio americano nativo que pode ser capaz de realizar seus desejos.

programme.title: Uma Aventura de Natal
programme.desc: O Natal na casa dos Nolan não é o que costumava ser. Em uma viagem de compras de última hora com papai, a família entra em uma loja encantada apenas para descobrir um globo de neve deslumbrante com poderes mágicos.

programme.title: 12 Dias De Presentes
programme.desc: Um homem ganha uma fortuna e decide compartilhar o prêmio com as pessoas de sua pequena cidade, mas ele não podia imaginar que o amor seria uma de suas recompensas.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.title: So this is Christmas
programme.desc: A los 18 años, Ashley sale con gente mala, y busca una fuga de la rutina de casa. Pero todo empieza a cambiar cuando uno de los empleados de la familia consigue animarla a hacer una pieza de teatro de Navidad para niños necesitados.

programme.title: Juntos esta Navidad
programme.desc: Luego de una ruptura amorosa, Isabel y el viudo Juan Andrés con su hija comparten, accidentalmente, una cabaña navideña. Circunstancias inusuales y la magia de las fiestas resultarán en una unión muy especial.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: Una Navidad de Cuento
programme.desc: En esta alegre versión del clásico de Dickens, Carol (Tori Spelling) interpreta a una presentadora de programas de televisión egoísta que está decidida a destruir la diversión festiva en el estudio. Por sus acciones, tres espíritus la visitarán.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.sub-title: Cliff Richard / Run D.M.C. / Michael Bublé / Chris Rea / Mariah Carey / Elton John

programme.title: MTV Xmas
programme.desc: Sia (Snowman) / Michael Bublé (It's Beginning to Look a Lot Like Christmas) / Boney M (Mary's Boy Child - Oh My Lord) / Ed Sheeran & Elton John (Merry Christmas) / Let it Snow! (Dean Martin) / Ariana Grande (Santa Tell Me)
programme.sub-title: Sia / Michael Bublé / Boney M / Ed Sheeran & Elton John / Dean Martin / Ariana Grande

programme.title: MTV Xmas
programme.desc: Mariah Carey (All I Want For Christmas Is You) / Andy Williams (It's The Most Wonderful Time Of The Year) / George Ezra (Come On Home For Christmas) / Sam Smith (Have Yourself A Merry Little Christmas) / Wham! (Last Christmas)
programme.sub-title: Mariah Carey / Andy Williams / George Ezra / Sam Smith / Wham! / Summer Walker & Love Renaissance / David Bowie & Bing Crosby

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.title: So this is Christmas
programme.desc: A los 18 años, Ashley sale con gente mala, y busca una fuga de la rutina de casa. Pero todo empieza a cambiar cuando uno de los empleados de la familia consigue animarla a hacer una pieza de teatro de Navidad para niños necesitados.

programme.title: Juntos esta Navidad
programme.desc: Luego de una ruptura amorosa, Isabel y el viudo Juan Andrés con su hija comparten, accidentalmente, una cabaña navideña. Circunstancias inusuales y la magia de las fiestas resultarán en una unión muy especial.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: Una Navidad de Cuento
programme.desc: En esta alegre versión del clásico de Dickens, Carol (Tori Spelling) interpreta a una presentadora de programas de televisión egoísta que está decidida a destruir la diversión festiva en el estudio. Por sus acciones, tres espíritus la visitarán.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: The Santa Squad
programme.desc: Allie, una profesora de arte desempleada, acepta un trabajo para ayudar a un viudo rico y a sus dos hijas. Mientras Allie levanta el espíritu navideño de la familia con adornos navideños, su amabilidad se ve recompensada con un regalo inesperado: ¡Amor!

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.title: So this is Christmas
programme.desc: A los 18 años, Ashley sale con gente mala, y busca una fuga de la rutina de casa. Pero todo empieza a cambiar cuando uno de los empleados de la familia consigue animarla a hacer una pieza de teatro de Navidad para niños necesitados.

programme.title: Juntos esta Navidad
programme.desc: Luego de una ruptura amorosa, Isabel y el viudo Juan Andrés con su hija comparten, accidentalmente, una cabaña navideña. Circunstancias inusuales y la magia de las fiestas resultarán en una unión muy especial.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: Una Navidad de Cuento
programme.desc: En esta alegre versión del clásico de Dickens, Carol (Tori Spelling) interpreta a una presentadora de programas de televisión egoísta que está decidida a destruir la diversión festiva en el estudio. Por sus acciones, tres espíritus la visitarán.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Kanadas Küstenwölfe
programme.desc: Der Great Bear Regenwald an der Westküste Kanadas ist die Heimat der Küstenwölfe. Sie haben felsige Riffe, bewaldete Inseln und die tobende Pazifikküste zu ihrer Heimat gemacht. Das besondere an ihnen ist, dass sie nicht nur an Land jagen, sondern auch im Ozean. Die Dokumentation begleitet Naturführer Cal Humchitt und sein Team auf den Spuren der Küstenwölfe.

programme.title: Naturparadiese in Lateinamerika: Die Anden
programme.desc: Diese Serie feiert Lateinamerikas dramatischste Regionen, von den Hohen Anden zum dampfenden Amazonas, von den windigen Steppen Patagoniens zu den Sümpfen Venezuelas – atemberaubende Schönheit und eine aufregende, vielfältige Tierwelt.

programme.title: Wildes Portugal: Von der Küste bis zu den Inseln
programme.desc: Der Reichtum von Portugals Küstengewässern ist erstaunlich. Tausende von Kreaturen leben am Atlantischen Ozean im Wasser und zu Land. Und die Inselwelt der Azoren mitten im Atlantik ist eines der reichsten Ökosysteme der Welt.

programme.title: Wildes Indonesien
programme.desc: Dieser Film erforscht die Inselwelt Indonesiens - ein Paradies von Riesenpflanzen und Korallengärten mit Drachen, Tigern und Riesenaffen, ein Zentrum biologischer Vielfalt, ein Land von Vulkanen und eine der letzten wilden Regionen.

programme.desc: Der Angler Jeremy Wade trotzt auf der Suche nach einem Monsterfisch der Strahlung in Tschernobyl.

programme.desc: Der Extremangler Jeremy Wade begibt sich auf eine Mission in Guyana in Südamerika.

programme.title: Tasmanien
programme.desc: Tasmanien ist ein einzigartiges Naturparadies: Wilde Strände, dichter Regenwald, zerklüftete Bergketten und alpine Moorlandschaften vereinen sich auf engstem Raum. Auf der Insel leben Wombats, Schnabeligel und Tasmanische Teufel. Die Rangerin Lalani Hyatt patrouilliert täglich durch das Arthur-Pieman-Schutzgebiet, bekämpft Waldbrände, stellt Umweltsünder oder rettet verwaiste Jungtiere.

programme.title: Indien Summer am Polarkreis
programme.desc: Der Herrgott, so ein Sprichwort in der Region, hat ihn nach der Schöpfung einfach vergessen: den Wald im Muddus Nationalpark in Schweden. Ein Urwald - die eine Hälfte voller Bäume, die andere voller Sümpfe und Seen, in dem die älteste Kiefer Schwedens steht. Wenn der Herbst die Bäume und Moose in goldgelbe und tiefrote Farbe taucht, spricht man auch hier im hohen Norden vom Indian Summer.

programme.title: Nach dem Wasser
programme.desc: Ein Erdbeben vor Sumatra löste 2004 den Tsunami aus. Der Film schildert die Umstände in der Region Aceh und wie die SOS-Kinderdörfer es schafften, Nothilfe zu leisten und bis heute mit ihren Programmen Kindern und Erwachsenen zu helfen.

programme.title: Burundi
programme.desc: Désiré Nininahazwe, Familienvater und Gründer eines Start ups, kam zum ersten Mal mit dem Trommeln in Kontakt, als er ins SOS-Kinderdorf nach Bujumbura kam, nachdem er seine Eltern im Bürgerkrieg verloren hatte.

programme.title: Madagaskar
programme.sub-title: Die junge Generation im Spannungsfeld des Klimawandels
programme.desc: Während man im westlichen Ausland an Vanilleplantagen und Tropenwälder denkt, spricht man in Madagaskar nur noch von Kéré, der schlimmsten Dürre seit 40 Jahren. Hoffnung gibt, dass sich die SOS-Kinderdörfer um die Kinder des Dorfes kümmern.

programme.title: Sri Lanka
programme.desc: Der fast 30 Jahre währende Bürgerkrieg im Süden Sri Lankas hat das Land verändert. Hunderte Kinder und Waisen standen auf der Straße. Dank der SOS-Kinderdörfer weltweit konnten die meisten in den sechs Kinderdörfern versorgt werden.

programme.title: Nach dem Wasser
programme.desc: Ein Erdbeben vor Sumatra löste 2004 den Tsunami aus. Der Film schildert die Umstände in der Region Aceh und wie die SOS-Kinderdörfer es schafften, Nothilfe zu leisten und bis heute mit ihren Programmen Kindern und Erwachsenen zu helfen.

programme.title: Kenia
programme.desc: Asha und Stephen sind im SOS-Kinderdorf in Nairobi aufgewachsen und haben das Beste daraus gemacht. Sie sind "The next Generation". Die Generation, die es schaffen will und auch schaffen wird.

programme.title: Waschbären, unsere neuen Nachbarn?
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Ursprünglich stammen Waschbären aus Nordamerika. Inzwischen breiten sie sich auch in Europa aus. Da sie 2016 von der EU als invasiv, also als Gefahr für das Ökosystem eingestuft wurden, werden sie massiv bejagt. Die Berliner Tierärztin Dr. Mathilde Laininger engagiert sich für ein friedliches Miteinander zwischen Mensch und Waschbär.

programme.title: Leben mit dem Tod
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Auf der indonesischen Insel Sulawesi dreht sich schon zu Lebzeiten der Bewohner alles die Beerdigung. Der Totenkult der Toraja kann viel Geld verschlingen, was die Bestattung verstorbener Verwandter oft auf Jahre unmöglich macht. So behalten die Angehörigen ihre Toten so lange im Haus, bis sie das Geld für die aufwendigen Feierlichkeiten haben.

programme.title: Pelota, die baskische Leidenschaft
programme.desc: Kaum eine Sportart verbindet die Menschen im Baskenland so sehr wie Pelota. Die Region im Grenzgebiet von Frankreich und Spanien, sieht sich als eigenständige Provinz mit einer gemeinsamen Kultur, Sprache und Identität. programme.title: Popa Chubby
programme.sub-title: Popa Chubby - It's A Mighty Hard Road
programme.desc: Popa Chubby, born as Ted Horowitz, is an American blues singer and guitarist, who has become one of the most popular figures of New York's blues scene. Early on in his career he released the album 'Booty and the Beast' (1995), which became one of the 1990s's best-selling blues albums. Chubby describes his own style as "The Stooges meets Buddy Guy, Motörhead meets Muddy Waters, and Jimi Hendrix meets Robert Johnson". As part of the French music festival Blues sur Seine, Chubby and his band played a great blues rock concert, showcasing the artist's powerful and soulful guitar playing. This performance was recorded at Théâtre Simone Signoret on November 8, 2019.

programme.title: Thelonious Monk
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Jimmy Witherspoon & Rozaa Wortham
programme.desc: Since 1977, Estival is a summer jazz festival in Switzerland, Lugano. Estival offers a thrilling and particularly surprising line-up that explores the rich world of contemporary music whilst promoting the understanding of different cultures, tolerance, and co-existence. Jimmy Witherspoon and Rozaa Wortham, two incredible brilliant jazz musicians. Rozaa Wortham starts off the show with the Jimmy Witherspoon Quartet. Swinging and full of energy she performs ‘It Don't Mean A Thing'. Jimmy Witherspoon, known for the song “Ain't Nobody's Business” ends the show with some astounding lean-back blues.

programme.title: Kenny Barron
programme.desc: Pianist Kenny Barron's June 27, 2019 appearance at the Alfa Jazz Festival in Ukraine's Lviv was a celebration of sublime jazz virtuosity. The revered elder statesmen of jazz piano brought his regular working trio of Kiyoshi Kitagawa (bass) and Jonathan Blake (drums), augmented by stellar jazzman Marcus Strickland (tenor saxophone) and young lion Riley Mulherkar (trumpet). Their seamless blend of classic bebop and modern explorations spoke of a deep, emotive connection to each note, captivating the Ukrainian audience with lyrical improvisations during this unforgettable concert.

programme.title: Jon Hendricks, Judith Hendricks, Kim Lindsay & Mart Ledford
programme.desc: Since 1977, Estival is a summer jazz festival in Switzerland, Lugano. Estival offers a thrilling and particularly surprising line-up that explores the rich world of contemporary music whilst promoting the understanding of different cultures, tolerance, and co-existence. John Carl Hendricks is one of the instigators of "vocalese", an art form that aims to add lyrics to existing instrumental pieces and replace several instruments with singing. He flaunts this technique at Estival, where he "scat" while playing double bass. Hendricks is known for his mastery of scat, a form of vocal jazz that uses onomatopoeia rather than lyrics

programme.title: Manu Dibango, Daniel Rallo, Jerry Malekani & Frederic Gaillardet
programme.sub-title: Soul Makossa: Manu Dibango in Stuttgart
programme.desc: Manu Dibango, one of Africa's biggest musical stars and top saxophonists, is an indispensable artist. He was one of the first African musicians to score a worldwide hit with his 1972 release “Soul Makossa”, paving the way for many other artists. The very concept of world music owes much to him. A superb stage performer with great communicative humour, Dibango is above all one of the founding fathers of a modern African musical style that is open to jazz, R&B, salsa, gospel, funk, and reggae. This concert showcases all these genres, and features an excellent line-up of musicians from the four corners of the planet.

programme.title: Gil Evans & Ornette Coleman
programme.sub-title: Gil Evans, Ornette Coleman - Schloss Ansbach
programme.desc: This program presents two concerts from Schloss Ansbach in 1978. The first concert features Gil Evans and his orchestra, consisting of Gil Evans on piano, Steve Lacy on soprano saxophone, Arthur Blythe on alto saxophone, Pit Levin on synthesizers, Earl McIntyre on trombone, Lewis Soloff on trumpet, Geoffrey Berlin on bass and Sue Evans on percussion instruments. The second concert features saxophonist Ornette Coleman at the peak of his musically expressive powers. Coleman is joined by Bern Nix on guitar, Charles Ellerbee on guitar, Albert Arnold on bass, and Shannon Jackson on drums and percussion.

programme.title: Raul Midón
programme.desc: Raul Midón appeared at 2017's Sing Jazz Festival in Singapore with double bassist Romeir Mendez and drummer Billy Williams. Blind since birth, Raul Midón is a singer, guitarist, and songwriter from New Mexico. With a vocal range as dynamic as his guitar playing and a remarkable talent for trumpet mimicry, Midón's performances transcend musical boundaries, effortlessly blending rock, jazz, folk, and Latin pop into his unique sound. He has worked with numerous legends, including Bill Withers, Herbie Hancock, Sting, and Dianne Reeves, and his album ‘Bad Ass and Blind' was nominated for a Grammy Award for Best Jazz Vocal Album in 2018. No wonder the Sing Jazz audience were ecstatic!

programme.title: Kenny G
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. In 1987, smooth jazz saxophonist and crowd-favorite Kenny G serenaded those attending the North Sea Jazz Festival in The Hague. After beginning his career in the Love Unlimited Orchestra, he now brings his own band for this hypnotic performance.

programme.title: Rod Stewart
programme.desc: Roderick David Stewart was born in Highgate North London as the Second World war was coming to a close. His neighbourhood was bombed just 30 minutes before his birth, giving him the feeling that he almost didn't make it into the world. One of Rod's earliest exposures to music was with the family gatherings around the piano in which they would sing songs by the 30s baritone singer, Al Jolson. The young Rod was also caught up in the wake of Rock and Roll music that swept 50s Britain. Rod developed a love of Otis Redding and Sam Cooke and took to the Blues circuit with his first band The Dimensions. However Rod lost vocal duties to Jimmy Powell and soon left the group but fate intervened in the form of singer Long John Baldry. Baldry brought Stewart into his band The Hoochie Coochie Men, but like many of Rod's musical projects in the mid 60s it was short lived. However Baldry and Stewart were soon back together as part of Steam Packet along with Julie Driscoll. Rod had embraced the Mod look by this stage and the nickname Rod the Mod began to stick as his recognition grew. After leaving Steam Packet Rod was quickly picked up by former Yard Birds guitarist Jeff Beck. Rod had been a fan of The Yard Birds and this opportunity not only gave him a chance to sing with a hero, but also tour extensively across the US in the late 60s. Whilst on tour with Jeff Beck, Rod met guitarist Ronnie Wood, the two remained friends and when the Jeff Beck group disbanded, Rod and Ronnie became part of a new band that would be key to the success of both of their careers, Faces Despite his success with Faces, Rod released his own debut solo album An Old Raincoat Won't Ever Let You Down. The bulk of which was recorded during his time in the Jeff Beck group Things would change dramatically for Stewart as a solo artist with the release of his third solo album 1971's Every Picture Tells A Story. The album would make him the first solo artist to achieve the number 1 position in both the US and the UK. And would give him his first smash hit single Maggie May Featuring archive material, music videos “Maggie May” “In The Morning” and, exclusive insights from music critics and journalists Michael Bonner (Uncut Magazine), Hamish MacBain (Shortlist), John Aizlewood (Evening Standard) Rock Legends Rod Stewart tells the story of one of Britain's enduring rock stars.

programme.title: Fleetwood Mac
programme.desc: The story of Fleetwood Mac is one of two halves. The first half began within the British blues scene of the late 1960s, where the band's founder, Peter Green, honed his talent. Peter Green asked fellow Bluesbreakers John McVie and Mick Fleetwood to form a new band after they successfully collaborated in the studio on an instrumental with Jeremy Spencer and Bob Brunning completing the line-up. They took on the new name of Fleetwood Mac. The band had success in the UK with their first two albums and in 1968, with the addition of guitarist, Danny Kirwan, they finally achieved their first number one single, Albatross. However, Fleetwood Mac's third album, They Play On, would be Peter Green's last with the band, Without Peter Green, Danny Kirwan would take on the lead role within the group In 1970, Christine McVie, the wife of John McVie was yet another addition, after having provided backing vocals and album artwork for the new line-up. Yet more changes came to the band's line-up with Kirwan sadly having to leave due to problems with alcoholism, Songwriter Bob Welch replaced him, but then departed shortly after. Fleetwood Mac with the line-up of Mick Fleetwood, Stevie Nicks, Lindsey Buckingham and John and Christine McVie entered its second chapter. In 1975 they released what would ironically be their second self-titled album, which would top the US Billboard chart and featured the hit single Rhiannon, written by Stevie Nicks But as the album reached number one in the US and began shifting units of over five million, the band's personal lives were becoming strained. In 1977 the band released Rumours. The lyrics of the songs written by each member of the band exposed the personal turmoil that existed within the group Rumours has, to date, sold over 45 million copies worldwide, making it one of the biggest selling albums of all time. Influenced by new wave and punk, Buckingham convinced the band to go for a more experimental approach for the highly-anticipated follow-up album, Tusk. Featuring archive material, music videos “Dreams” “Landslide” and, exclusive insights from music critics and journalists Michael Bonner (Uncut Magazine), Hamish MacBain (Shortlist), John Aizlewood (Evening Standard)

programme.title: Genesis
programme.desc: An English rock band formed at Charterhouse School, Godalming, Surrey in 1967. The band underwent many changes in musical style over its career, from folk music to progressive rock in the 1970s, before moving towards pop at the end of the decade. They have sold 21.5 million RIAA-certified albums in the US and their worldwide sales are estimated to be between 100 million and 150 million. Featuring archive material, music videos and, exclusive insights from music critics and journalists Michael Bonner (Uncut Magazine), Hamish MacBain (Shortlist), John Aizlewood (Evening Standard)

programme.title: Tom Petty
programme.desc: Tom Petty was the lead singer of Tom Petty and the Heartbreakers, formed in 1976. He was also a co-founder of the late 1980s supergroup the Traveling Wilburys. He recorded many hit singles with the Heartbreakers and as a solo artist. In his career, he sold more than 80 million records worldwide, making him one of the best-selling music artists of all time. He was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 2001. He was found unconscious at his home, not breathing and in full cardiac arrest, early in the morning of October 2, 2017. He was taken to the UCLA Medical Center in Santa Monica, California, where he died at 8:40 pm that evening by accidental death by a combination of pain killers.

programme.title: Janis Joplin
programme.desc: Janis Joplin was one of the most successful and widely-known female rock stars of her era. After releasing three albums, she died of a heroin overdose at the age of 27. Her fourth album, Pearl, was released in January 1971, just over three months after her death. It reached number one on the Billboard charts. Her Legacy. The big-voiced, bluesy singer dominated the stage, forged her own path and paved the way for the female singers who followed.

programme.title: Leonardo García Alarcón, Cappella Mediterranea & Mariana Flores
programme.sub-title: Vocal baroque works by Cavalli, Strozzi & Bembo
programme.desc: Argentinian conductor and harpsichordist Leonardo García Alarcón leads his ensemble Cappella Mediterranea in a program of Italian Baroque music. The ensemble performs some of the finest Baroque pieces composed by Francesco Cavalli, a prominent composer in 17th-century Venice, and two of his famous students, Barbara Strozzi and Antonia Bembo. Argentinian soprano Mariana Flores presents the vocal works. On the program are ‘Mira questi due lumi' from Cavalli's Le nozze di Teti e di Peleo, ‘Dimmi, Amor, che farò' from L'Oristeo, ‘Sinfonia della notte' from L'Egisto, and ‘E vuol dunque Ciprigna' from Ercole Amante ‘M'ingannasti in verità' from Bembo's Produzioni armoniche consacrate a Luigi XIV Strozzi's Sino alla morte, Che si può fare, Lagrime mie, L'amante segreto, and è Pazzo il moi core Biagio Marini's La Romanesca Tarquinio Merula's Aria Sopra La Cieccona and Dario Castello's Sonata Seconda. This performance was recorded at the magnificent Église Notre-Dame of Sablé-sur-Sarthe, France, on August 26, 2020.

programme.title: Les Arts Florissants & Paul Agnew
programme.desc: Italian composer Claudio Monteverdi (1567-1643) composed nine books of madrigals in half a century, which helped transform the genre from the polyphonic, a cappella madrigals of the late Renaissance to the ‘concertato' madrigals of the early Baroque, shifting the style's focus to the ability of music to express emotions contained in a text. In 2011, British tenor Paul Agnew and renowned Baroque ensemble Les Arts Florissants started recording eight books of Monteverdi's madrigals. In this program, Agnew leads Les Arts Florissants in the madrigals of Book I. Published on New Year's day of 1587, Book I consist of seventeen madrigals for five voices. This performance was recorded at the Cité de la musique in Paris, France, in 2011.

programme.title: Martha Argerich, Evgeny Kissin, Iddo Bar-Shai & Arielle Beck
programme.sub-title: Martha Argerich – A Birthday Celebration - I
programme.desc: On the occasion of her 80th birthday, Argentinian pianist Martha Argerich explored chamber music repertoire in this wonderful concert, recorded at Château de Chantilly, France. The ‘Grande Dame' of the piano is joined by various renowned artists, including pianists Evgeny Kissin, Iddo Bar-Shaï, and Arielle Beck violinists Gidon Kremer, Maxim Vengerov, and Tedi Papavrami cellist Mischa Maisky, Flugelhorn player Sergei Nakariakov, as well as her daughter and grandson: Lyda Chen-Argerich (piano and viola) and David Chen-Argerich (piano). On the program are Alfred Schnittke's Congratulatory rondo for piano and violin Preludes No. 5, 21, and 24 from Mieczysław Weinberg's 24 Preludes, Op. 100 (arranged for solo violin by G. Kremer) ‘Waltz' and ‘Slava' from Sergei Rachmaninoff's 6 Morceaux, Op. 11, and Romance for six hands Fritz Kreisler's Liebesleid Robert Schumann's Fantasiestücke Op. 73, and Piano Quintet in E-flat major, Op. 44 and ‘Laideronnette, impératrice des Pagodes' from Maurice Ravel's Ma mère l'Oye. This performance was recorded on June 11, 2021.

programme.title: Tuva Semmingsen, Klaus Tönshoff, Danish National Symphony Orchestra & DR Big Band
programme.desc: Musicians of the Danish National Symphony Orchestra, the DR Big Band, and the Danish National Vocal Ensemble join forces under the baton of Klaus Tönshoff in this dazzling concert featuring great songs from black and white cinema. Norwegian mezzosoprano Tuva Semmingsen sings ‘Diamonds Are A Girl's Best Friend', from Gentlemen Prefer Blondes, ‘My Favorite Things' from The Sound of Music, ‘Over the Rainbow' from The Wizard of Oz, ‘Moon River' from Breakfast at Tiffany's, and many other unforgettable hits. This concert performance was recorded at the DR Koncerthuset in Copenhagen, Denmark, in June 2020.

programme.title: Maria Luigia Borsi & Antonio Artese
programme.sub-title: Vocal works by Puccini, Leoncavallo a. o.
programme.desc: The six-concert series “Io suono italiano” is dedicated to music of Italian composers and performed by Italian musicians on Italian instruments. The concert programs cover four centuries of music: from Girolamo Frescobaldi and Antonio Vivaldi to more contemporary music by Ennio Morricone and Azio Corghi. Each program presents more familiar pieces alongside lesser-known compositions. These performances were filmed at the atmospheric Teatro Sociale in Rovigo, Italy, in January 2021. In this program, Maria Luigia Borsi (soprano) and Antonio Artese (piano) present a recital consisting of several songs and arias. On the program are Francesco Paolo Tosti's Sogno, ‘A vucchella, and L'alba separa dalla luce l'ombra Giacomo Puccini's Sole e amore, Sogno d'or, “Donde lieta” (from La Bohème), “Il bel sogno di Doretta” (from La rondine), and “O mio babbino caro” (from Gianni Schicchi) Renato Brogi's Presentimento, Ruggero Leoncavallo's Mattinata, and Alfredo Catalini's Chanson Groenlandaise.

programme.title: Jos van Immerseel, Anima Eterna Brugge, Claron McFadden & Bart Van Caenegem
programme.desc: Belgian conductor Jos van Immerseel leads Anima Eterna Brugge in a concert program dedicated to American composer George Gershwin. The program opens with Gershwin's symphonic suite Catfish Row (arr. Steven D. Bowen) which is based upon music from his famous opera Porgy and Bess (1935). This is followed by the well-known tone poem An American in Paris (1928). After, soprano Claron McFadden joins the orchestra, presenting a selection of Gershwin's classic jazz songs, including ‘The man I love' (1924-27), ‘I got rhythm' (1930), and ‘By Strauss' (1936). She also performs ‘My man's gone now' and ‘Summertime' from Porgy and Bess. The concert ends with Gershwin's celebrated Rhapsody in Blue, with Bart Van Caenegem as featured pianist. This performance was recorded at Concertgebouw Brugge, Belgium, on March 3, 2017.

programme.title: Kinderstube Wildnis Bei den Bären
programme.desc: Mitten im Winterschlaf - versteckt unter einer dichten Schneedecke - kommen die drei kleinen Schwarzbären Sam, Sophie und Sybil zur Welt. Ihre ersten Wochen verbringen die noch nackten und blinden Babys im Schutz der geräumigen Höhle. Sobald die Tage länger werden, lugen die inzwischen flauschigen Bärenkinder zum ersten Mal aus dem Bau und für die ausgehungerte Bärin wird es Zeit, die Reserven wieder aufzufüllen. Obwohl im Wald viele Gefahren lauern, muss sie bald aufbrechen. Für den Bären-Nachwuchs sind die Ausflüge die reinsten Abenteuer. Während die Mutter besorgt nach Raubtieren Ausschau hält, toben sie fröhlich durchs Unterholz. Neben der Suche nach Essbarem hat die Mutter es nicht leicht, ihre verspielte Rasselbande zusammenzuhalten. Ohne den Schutz der Mutter sind die noch viel zu kleinen Bärchen aber hoffnungslos verloren. Ausgewachsene Schwarzbären haben kaum natürliche Feinde, aber als Jungtiere sind sie für Adler und Wölfe leichte Beute. Nur zwanzig Prozent überleben überhaupt den ersten Geburtstag. Plötzlich bricht nur unweit der Höhle auch noch Feuer im Wald aus...

programme.title: Kinderstube Wildnis Bei den Löwen
programme.desc: Eine alleinerziehende Löwin hat es nicht leicht in Afrikas Savannen. Löwen-Mama Nyota hat keine Beschützer und muss für sich und ihren fünf Monate alten Sohn Moja ganz alleine sorgen. Vor der Regenzeit sind Beutetiere spärlich und die besten Reviere von großen Löwenrudeln besetzt. Auf sich alleine gestellt, muss Nyota zwischen ihrem knurrenden Magen und dem Schutz des Kleinen abwägen. Es gelingt ihr kaum, sich einmal satt zu essen. Entweder die Jagdversuche bleiben erfolglos oder Hyänen machen ihr das mühsam erlegte Wild nach wenigen Bissen streitig. Alleine hat sie den Aasfressern kaum etwas entgegen zu setzen. Um Moja nicht in Gefahr zu bringen, verzichtet sie jedoch auf einen Kampf und überlässt ihren Fang der gierigen Meute. Berührende Szenen zeigen, wie das Duo trotz der immer weiter schwindenden Kräfte auch in den härtesten Wochen zusammenhält. Die Rettung der kleinen Familie naht in Form der heraufziehenden Gnu-Herden.

programme.title: Kinderstube Wildnis Bei den Affen
programme.desc: Die Tonka-Makaken bevölkern die Tempel auf Sri Lanka. In einem der Clans erblickt das kleine Affen-Mädchen Gremlin das Licht der Welt. Von Geburt an muss es sich in dem lauten Gewusel aus Familienbanden und Fehden mit benachbarten Truppen behaupten. Das Gruppenleben ist von einer strengen Hierarchie bestimmt. Die Machtkämpfe zwischen und innerhalb der Familienverbände bergen ebenso viele Gefahren wie lauernde Greifvögel und die angrenzende Straße. Allzu oft geraten die noch wehrlosen Babys zwischen die Fronten. Bei Übergriffen durch Ranghöhere müssen Mütter oft zusehen, wie unsanft mit ihrem Nachwuchs umgegangen wird. Nur jedes dritte Makaken-Kind kann sich durchsetzen und überlebt seine ersten Monate. Der niedrige Rang der Mutter und obendrein ihre auffällige weiße Schwanzspitze sind nicht die besten Voraussetzungen für die kleine Gremlin. Doch das aufgeweckte Äffchen lernt schnell dazu und entpuppt sich als wahre Kämpfernatur.

programme.title: Kinderstube Wildnis Bei den Elefanten
programme.desc: Pünktlich zur Regenzeit versammeln sich unzählige Dickhäuter im ostafrikanischen Samburu Nationalpark. Wenn es genügend Gräser, Sträucher und Wasserstellen gibt, bekommen die Elefanten ihren Nachwuchs. Auch Maya kommt als erstes Baby einer jungen Elefantenkuh zur Welt. Nach der ersten Portion Milch und einem kühlenden Schlammbad machen sich Mutter und Kind auf den Weg zurück zur Herde. Der Neuzugang wird euphorisch von allen Familien-Mitgliedern begrüßt. Die Freundschaften und Bindungen, die in der Gruppe entstehen, halten bei den Dickhäutern ein Leben lang. Bis zum Beginn der Trockenzeit bleiben Maya ein paar herrliche Wochen nur zum Spielen und krafttanken im sicheren Reservat. Pünktlich zum Aufbruch der Herden am Ende der Regenzeit, müssen die Kleinen stark genug für die erste lange Wanderung sein. Die geplanten Routen sind voller Gefahren: Reißende Flüsse voll lauernder Krokodile, hungrige Löwen und Wilderer außerhalb des Nationalparks werden zur nervenaufreibenden Bewährungsprobe für Maya.
